<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1074</anchor> <rss>dannypsnl.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>dannypsnl</addr>  <route>dannypsnl.xml</route>   <title>Lîm Tsú-thuàn</title> <meta name="external">https://dannypsnl.me/</meta><meta name="position">Compiler Developer</meta><meta name="institution">Second State</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1075</anchor> <rss>jms-009Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Changelog</taxon> <addr>jms-009Q</addr>  <route>jms-009Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Forester 2.5 [unreleased]</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Thanks to <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> and <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link> for their suggestions and bug reports on the <link href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss" type="external">mailing list</link>.</p><ul>  <li>A new <code>\iftex</code> command has been added, following a suggestion of <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link>; this can be used to control the behavior of macros, depending on whether they are being rendered by <tex>\LaTeX</tex> or by the browser. For example, <code>\iftex{foo}{bar}</code> will become <code>foo</code> when passed to the <tex>\LaTeX</tex> tool, but will be reated as <code>bar</code> when rendering for the browser.</li>  <li>A new <link href="jms-005O.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.1">fluid binding</link> <code>\transclude/taxon</code> has been added to the <link href="jms-0067.xml" type="local" title="Flexible transclusion options in Forester 2.2">transclusion overrides</link>, which can be used to locally change the taxon of a transcluded tree. Thanks to <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> for implementing this.</li>  <li>In order to support more modular development of <link href="tfmt-000V.xml" type="local" title="Forests of evergreen notes">forests</link>, a new <code>theme</code> directory is expected to contain all the XSL, CSS, font, etc. assets that pertain to the <em>presentation</em> of your <link href="tfmt-000V.xml" type="local" title="Forests of evergreen notes">forest</link>; the <code>assets</code> directory is meant to store things like images, PDFs, etc. that pertain to the <em>content</em> of your <link href="tfmt-000V.xml" type="local" title="Forests of evergreen notes">forest</link>. The simplest way to take advantage of this new feature is to bind your <code>theme</code> directory to a <link href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Submodules" type="external">git submodule</link> pointing to the <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme" type="external">forester-base-theme</link> repository. Your existing <link href="tfmt-000V.xml" type="local" title="Forests of evergreen notes">forest</link> will still work fine for now even if you do not migrate to the new directory structure.</li></ul></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1076</anchor> <rss>jms-009H.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-009H</addr>  <route>jms-009H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>22</day></date>  <title>List of <link href="tfmt-000R.xml" type="local" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><ul>  <li><link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link>: <link href="https://dannypsnl.me/index.xml" type="external">dannypsnl.me</link></li>  <li><link href="masanoriogino.xml" type="local" title="Masanori Ogino">Masanori Ogino</link>: <link href="https://trail.brackets-salad.com/index.xml" type="external">trail.brackets-salad.com</link></li>  <li><link href="yueniu.xml" type="local" title="Yue Niu">Yue Niu</link>: <link href="https://yuesforest.com/index.xml" type="external">yuesforest.com</link></li>  <li><link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local" title="Riley Shahar">Riley Shahar</link>: <link href="https://rileyshahar.com" type="external">rileyshahar.com</link></li>  <li><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</link>: <link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com" type="external">jonmsterling.com</link></li>  <li><link href="ayberktosun.xml" type="local" title="Ayberk Tosun">Ayberk Tosun</link>:
  <link href="https://ayberkt.github.io/mathematical-forest/" type="external">ayberktosun.github.io/mathematical-forest</link></li>  <li>Zifan Wang: <link href="https://chry-santhemum.github.io/forest/" type="external">chry-santhemum.github.io/forest</link></li>  <li>Bernardo Hummes Flores: <link href="https://birromer.github.io" type="external">birromer.github.io</link></li></ul></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>